<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634078955499190716" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634078970401976844">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement1" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[The example]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p>Select a new dock style in the 'Dock style for StatusBar' ComboBox and the docking style of the <em>StatusBar </em>will be changed.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Header Code="HeaderElement2" Type="Subtitle" ShowInTOC="0"><![CDATA[General Info]]></Header>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p>Visual WebGui <em>StatusBar </em>can be docked to any window pane or be displayed floating. The <em>StatusBar </em>contains the<em> Dock</em> property that defines the controls docking style. The <em>StatusBar </em>can have the following docking styles:<br /><strong>None </strong>- the <em>StatusBar </em>is not docked.<br /><strong>Fill </strong>&ndash; all the <em>StatusBar</em>'s edges are docked to the all edges of its containing control and sized appropriately.<br /><strong>Top </strong>- the <em>StatusBar</em>'s top edge is docked to the top of its containing control.<br /><strong>Right </strong>- the <em>StatusBar</em>'s right edge is docked to the right edge of its containing control.<br /><strong>Bottom </strong>- the <em>StatusBar</em>'s bottom edge is docked to the bottom of its containing control.<br /><strong>Left </strong>- the <em>StatusBar</em>'s left edge is docked to the left edge of its containing control.<br />&nbsp;</p>]]></Paragraph>
  </Nodes>
</Data>